==Old English==
===Etymology===
Uncertain origin: cognate with Old Saxon [[huþ|hūþ]], Old High German [[-hude]] (found in place-names).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/hy:θ/}}

===Noun===
{{Unicode|'''hȳþ'''}} ''f'' (plural {{Unicode|'''[[hyþa|hȳþa]]'''}} or {{Unicode|'''[[hyþe|hȳþe]]'''}})
# a [[harbour]] or landing-place, a [[hithe]]
#:''Comon ðær þry men to ðære hyðe'': three men came to the landing-place.  (''St Guthlac'')

===Descendants===
*English [[hithe]]

